             <tr> 
              <td align="left" style="padding: 0px 40px 0px 0px; text-align: left;" valign="top" width="418"> 
               <div style="line-height: 24px; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(26, 26, 26); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 24px;">
                <br> 
                <span style="color: rgb(26, 26, 26); font-size: 24px; line-height: 24px;">IRIS Welcomes Bob Detrick</span>
                <br> 
                <span style="color: rgb(26, 26, 26); font-size: 16px; line-height: 16px;">New Consortium President Appointed by Board</span>
                <br> 
                <br> 
                <img align="none" alt="new_prez" border="0" height="198" hspace="0" src="https://cc286088d6-custmedia.vresp.com/03a7240c98/new_prez.jpg" style="width: 371px; height: 198px;" title="new_prez" vspace="0" width="371">
                <br> 
                <span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; line-height: 15px;">In early April, IRIS Board of Directors Chair, Professor Anne Meltzer, announced the appointment of&nbsp;Dr. Robert S. Detrick as IRIS&nbsp;President. Detrick started work at IRIS on&nbsp;April 28, taking over from Dr. David Simpson, who served as IRIS President since July 1991. Detrick is a marine geophysicist, and most recently served as Assistant Administrator at NOAA's Office of Oceanic and Atmospheric Research and acting NOAA Chief Scientist. Prior to joining NOAA, Detrick was the director of NSF's Division of Earth Sciences. He joined NSF in 2008 following more than 20 years at Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution where he was a senior scientist, department chair, and vice president for marine facilities and operation. &nbsp;<a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/timeless/story/new_president">Read more</a>.</span>
                <br> 
                <br> 
                <br> 
                <span style="color: rgb(26, 26, 26); font-size: 24px; line-height: 24px;">IRIS Announces the David Simpson Fund for Innovation</span>
                <br> 
                <br> 
                <img align="none" alt="fund_graphic" border="0" height="198" hspace="0" src="https://cc286088d6-custmedia.vresp.com/03a7240c98/fund_graphic.jpg" style="width: 371px; height: 198px;" title="fund_graphic" vspace="0" width="371"> 
                <div style="line-height: 24px; margin: 0px 20px 10px 0px; color: rgb(26, 26, 26); font-size: 24px;">
                 <span style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">To encourage and sustain the spirit of innovation and community engagement that is the hallmark of IRIS, the Board of Directors has established an Innovation Fund in honor of David Simpson as he completes his 23 years of service as IRIS president. The intent of the Fund is to provide the Consortium with a source of unrestricted funds that the Board can designate to stimulate new initiatives and develop new ventures. Emphasis will be placed on ways to increase community outreach and leverage development of new resources that expand the Consortium's reach by supporting early career scientists, expanding international engagement, enhancing the visibility of research in seismology, and developing interactions with industry. Please </span>
                 <a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/fundraisers/2014/david_simpson_fund_innovation/" style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 15px; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">donate now</a>
                 <span style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 15px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"> and participate in this exciting opportunity!</span>
                </div> 
                <br> 2014 IRIS Workshop
               </div> 
               <div style="line-height: 16px; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(26, 26, 26); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;">
                Registration Deadline is May 16
               </div> 
               <div style="line-height: 0px;">
                <img align="none" alt="iris_2014_wksp_nl" border="0" height="198" hspace="0" src="https://cc286088d6-custmedia.vresp.com/b61ac14712/iris_2014_wksp_nl.jpg" style="display: block; width: 371px; height: 198px;" title="iris_2014_wksp_nl" vspace="10" width="371">
               </div> 
               <div style="line-height: 15px; color: rgb(71, 71, 71); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px;"> 
                <div style="margin: 0 0 10px 0">
                 <span style="font-size:8pt;"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Arial, sans-serif;"><a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/meetings/2014/06/iris_workshop_sunriver_oregon/index.php">Registration is now open&nbsp;for the 2014 IRIS Workshop,</a>&nbsp; Four sessions anchor the meeting: (1) Science Challenges, (2) Very Wide Aperture Arrays: PBO, USArray, and Others, (3) Dirt, Data, Desktop, and Dissemination, and (4) Unexpected Science: New Approaches to Using Continuous Array Data. The meeting kicks off on Sunday, June 8 with three parallel symposia: Data Services Workshop, Educational Affiliates, and Early Career Investigators Meeting, followed by a field trip to Newberry Volcano. Please come and join us!<br> &nbsp;</span></span>
                </div> 
               </div> </td> 
              <td align="left" bgcolor="#cdde9f" style="padding: 15px 10px 10px; text-align: left;" valign="top" width="200"> 
               <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"> 
                <div style="background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159); margin: 0px 0px 10px;"> 
                 <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px;">
                  &nbsp; 
                  <div style="background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159); margin: 0px 0px 10px;"> 
                   <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px;">
                    <span style="font-size:10pt;"><strong style="line-height: 13px; color: rgb(75, 0, 130);"><a href="http://earthscope.org/events/earthscope-symposium-and-reception"><span style="color: rgb(75, 0, 130);">EarthScope Decade Symposium&nbsp;and Receptio</span></a><a href="http://www.earthscope.org/information/meetings-events/other/earthscope-symposium-and-reception" style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="color: rgb(75, 0, 130);">n</span></a></strong></span>
                   </div> 
                  </div> 
                  <div style="background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159); margin: 0px 0px 10px;"> 
                   <div style="line-height: 13px; margin: 0px 0px 10px;">
                    <span style="font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong>May 15, 2014</strong><br> Washington, DC</span>
                    <br> &nbsp;
                   </div> 
                  </div> 
                  <strong style="line-height: 13px; color: rgb(75, 0, 130);"><font size="2">IRIS Provides Input on NAS Decadal Survey of Ocean Sciences</font></strong>
                  <br> 
                  <span style="font-size: 10px; background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159);">The IRIS Board of Directors&nbsp;sent a letter to the National Academy of Sciences describing the need for data collection in the ocean&nbsp;to address the Seismological Grand Challenges.</span>
                  <br> 
                  <br> 
                  <br> 
                  <a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/news/story/happy_30th_birthday_iris"><strong style="background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159); line-height: 13px; color: rgb(75, 0, 130);"><u><font size="2">IRIS 30th Anniversary</font></u></strong></a>
                  <br style="background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159);"> 
                  <span style="font-size: 10px; background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159);">IRIS celebreated its 30th anniversary on May 8. <a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/news/story/happy_30th_birthday_iris">Read more</a>&nbsp;about how it all began.</span>
                  <br> 
                  <br> 
                  <br> 
                  <span style="font-size:10pt;"><strong style="background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159); font-size: 10pt; line-height: 13px; color: rgb(75, 0, 130);"><u><a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/news/story/iris_bids_farewell_to_passcal_program_manager_james_gridley"><span style="color: rgb(75, 0, 130);">James Gridlay Departs PASSCAL</span></a></u></strong></span>
                  <br style="background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159);"> 
                  <span style="font-size: 10px; background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159);">PASSCAL Program Manager James Gridley left his position at IRIS to join Pinnacle, part of Halliburton.&nbsp;<a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/news/story/iris_bids_farewell_to_passcal_program_manager_james_gridley">Read more</a>.</span>
                  <br> &nbsp;
                 </div> 
                </div> 
                <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px;"> 
                 <div style="line-height: 13px; margin: 0px 0px 10px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">
                  <a href="https://iris-industry-meeting.eventbrite.com" style="font-size: 12px;"><strong><span style="color:#4B0082;"><span style="font-size: 11px; line-height: 13px; background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159);"><span style="font-size:10pt;line-height: 13px;">Active Uses of Passive Seismic Data: Dirt to Desktop Exploration of Rock Properties, Structure, and Seismicity</span></span></span></strong></a>
                  <br> 
                  <br> 
                  <span style="font-size: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); line-height: 13px; background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159);"><strong>June 3, 2014</strong><br> Houston, TX</span>
                  <br> 
                  <br> 
                  <br> 
                  <a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLD4D607C2FA317E6D"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong style="line-height: 13px; color: rgb(75, 0, 130);"><span style="color:#4B0082;">IRIS Webinars</span></strong></span></a> 
                  <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px;"> 
                   <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px;"> 
                    <div style="line-height: 11px; margin: 0px 0px 10px;">
